.TH man 1 "2014" "1.0" "Unlimited digits calculator man page"
.SH NAME
Unlimited digits calculator
.SH SYNOPSIS
INSTALLATION:

make [OPTION]

Usable in folder with Makefile only.

CALCULATOR COMMANDS:

[COMMAND]

.SH DESCRIPTION
This project realizes calculator with unlimited number of digits before and after the decimal point. Digits are saved in strings. Calculator can process expressions of addition, subtraction and multiplication with arbitrarily nested brackets. Also has large input and output options.
For more information you can acces the code documentation (once created) from doc/index.html
.SH OPTIONS
INSTALLATION:

all - Compiles the code and creates documentation.

compile - Compiles the code only

doc - Creates the documentation only

run - Starts the calculator (once compiled)

clean - Removes the compiled code and the documentation

CALCULATOR COMMANDS:

std - sets input to standard input, you will be asked to directly enter expression.

file - sets input from file, you will be asked to enter name of file and lines you want to calculate.

output - changes the output, you will be asked to enter name of output file. You can also leave this empty to set standard output.

exit - exits the calculator
.SH EXAMPLES
make compile - First compile the code.

make run - Start the calculator, you will be asked to enter type of input.

std - Choose input to standard input, then you will be asked to enter expression.

5+5+5*(2-2*(2+5)+1)+1 - Random entered expression, result will be shown in standard output. Then you will be again asked to enter another input. You can also choose input from file by typing "file".

.SH SEE ALSO
INSTALL.txt, README.txt, LICENSE.txt
